+{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01PKE5MSmikKZfHCgpZ6ja9w","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I have a clear picture of all root causes. Let me document them:\n\n**Root Causes Identified:**\n\n1. **`OrderRepository.update`** (repository.ts:38): Does `{ ...updates, id, updatedAt }` — this discards all existing fields not in `updates`. Should be `{ ...existing, ...updates, id, updatedAt }`.\n\n2. **`OrderService.cancelOrder`** (service.ts:78): `order.items.map(...)` fails because `findById` returns a copy of the order, but after `update()` is broken, the returned order from `findById` is missing `items`. Actually — the real issue is that `cancelOrder` calls `findById` which gets the current stored order. The `update` method is broken (bug #1), so once an order is `confirmed` via `update`, the stored version has no `items`, `customerId`, etc. This cascades.\n\n3. **`InventoryService.handleOrderCancelled`** (inventory/service.ts:50): Checks `eventWithItems.status !== 'cancelled'` but the cancellation event doesn't include `status` field — it contains `orderId`, `reason`, `items`, `timestamp`. So the guard always returns early, never releasing stock.\n\n4. **`BillingService.handleRefund`** (billing/service.ts:25,62): Registered as `this.eventBus.on(ORDER_EVENTS.REFUNDED, this.handleRefund)` — missing `.bind(this)`, so `this.payments` is undefined when called.\n\n5. **`calculateOrderTotal`** (calculator.ts:23): `total = afterDiscount + taxAmount` — doesn't round the final total. The test expects `130.86` but gets `130.87` due to floating-point accumulation.\n\n6. **`OrderService.refundOrder`** (service.ts:99): Uses `>= REFUND_WINDOW_DAYS` but the test \"allows refund on exactly day 30\" expects day 30 to be allowed. Should use `> REFUND_WINDOW_DAYS`."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":7234,"cache_read_input_tokens":31004,"cache_creati